Leetcode-739... Daily temperatures
Brute force approach:
1. Start the loop from 0th index
2. Start the another loop (nested) from i+1th to end
3. Check if the nested loop's element is greater than ith value, if it is, add j-i to the ans array, if not add 0 to the lsit
class Solution {
    public int[] dailyTemperatures(int[] temp) {
        int n = temp.length;
        int[] ans = new int[n];

        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++) {
            for(int j=i+1; j<n ; j++) {
                if (temp[j] > temp[i]) {
                    ans[i] = j-i;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}

Optimal approach:
1. Declare a stack
2. Loop from 0th index of temp to end
3. Go until stack is not empty and i is greater than peek
4. Set the ans index
5. Push the new element to stack
class Solution {
    public int[] dailyTemperatures(int[] temp) {
        int n = temp.length;
        int[] ans = new int[n];
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>(); // store indices

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) {
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && temp[i]>temp[stack.peek()]) {
                int idx = stack.pop();
                ans[idx] = i-idx;
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
